svg.title: 3. Map Marble Park
svg.text: The Marble industry produces large amount of waste during mining and processing stages. This waste is dumped on to open land which creates a lot of en-vironmental problems. Not only for ecological reasons, but also in terms of reusing the very spe-cial and local material, the pro-longation of the stone’s lifecycle is highly demanded.

The link between education and industry today is more importnat than since ever. Local specific jobs and an early connection between the two sectors links the people more to their home-town and provides specialized workforce. Experienced people, who can give their knowledge to the following generations is cru-cial for the surviving of local industries.

The use of local material saves you both money and time. Shor-ter transportation ways means less emissions and a quicker availability. Furthermore it gives the object or the site, the materi-al was used for/at a special and local touch, which is often an advantage to generate higher tourism numbers.
